m. Fix by delivering the system prompt through the dedicated, already-wired channel (`openai-model-client.ts:31-38` already does `system: input.system`; `ModelStreamInput` already has `system`):\n\n- **`apps/api/src/chats/context-builder.ts`** — change `buildContext` to return `{ system: string; messages: ModelMessage[] }`: `system` is the stable prompt; `messages` is history only (drop the `{ role: 'system', ... }` push at lines 118-121). Keep ordering, trimming, sender-attribution, `partsToText` unchanged.\n- **`apps/api/src/chats/chat-loop.service.ts`** — `persistUserAndBuildContext` returns `{ system, messages }`; `createMessageStream` calls `client.streamText({ system, messages, abortSignal, onError, onFinish })` (line 59). No `ModelClient` interface change needed (`system` already in `ModelStreamInput`).\n- **`apps/api/src/chats/context-builder.spec.ts`** — rework the assertions coupled to \"system is `result[0]`\": byte-identical / no-per-request-data tests now target `.system`; order/cap/attribution tests target `.messages` (e.g. cap becomes `messages.length <= 10`, no leading system entry).\n\nKeeping v7's strict default ON means any *stray* `role: 'system'` message that ever lands in stored history (the `StoredMessage.role` union permits it) is caught as an error rather than silently forwarded — defense-in-depth, consistent with the repo's fail-closed posture.\n\nVerify **`apps/api/src/models/model-client.spec.ts`** still passes unchanged: it tests `openai-model-client`'s forwarding directly (asserts `streamText` called with `system: 'stable system'`), which this change doesn't alter — but confirm.\n\n## Verified non-issues (do NOT chase these)\n\nInventory-confirmed the following documented breaking changes have zero footprint in our code:\n- `convertToModelMessages` async (v6) — not used anywhere.\n- `CoreMessage` → `ModelMessage` (v6) — already on `ModelMessage`.\n- Tool-UI-part helper renames `isToolUIPart` etc. (v6/v7) — not used; web discriminates on